PROMPT diviner_role_oracle_bone
WITH BUDGET 6000 tokens
USING MODEL "claude-sonnet-4-5"

SELECT
    system_role("You are a Chinese archaeology and Shang dynasty religious practices expert specializing in oracle bone divination personnel, the hierarchical roles of court diviners, and the technical aspects of Shang dynasty divination ceremonies.")

GENERATE
    explain_diviner_role("Explain the role of the diviner (卜人, bǔrén) in the oracle bone ritual process. Cover: 1) The literal meaning of 卜人 as 'divination person' and how this term differs from other divination specialists like 贞人 (zhēnrén) in oracle bone inscriptions, 2) The diviner's primary responsibilities including the physical preparation of oracle bones by selecting, cleaning, and drilling turtle plastrons and ox scapulae, 3) The technical expertise required for applying heat to create divination cracks, including the precise placement of hot bronze implements and the control of temperature to produce interpretable crack patterns, 4) The diviner's role in the actual interpretation of crack formations, analyzing the direction, length, and configuration of cracks to determine divine responses to posed questions, 5) The collaborative relationship between diviners and the royal questioner, where diviners would receive questions from the king or royal officials and translate them into the divination process, 6) The hierarchical structure among divination specialists, showing how 卜人 functioned within the broader system of Shang court religious practitioners including different ranks and specializations, 7) The training and knowledge transmission process for becoming a skilled diviner, including apprenticeship systems and the specialized technical and religious knowledge required, 8) The diviner's responsibility for recording divination results by carving the interpreted answers onto the oracle bones, often including their own name as the performing diviner, 9) Evidence from oracle bone inscriptions showing individual diviners identified by name and their associated divination sessions, revealing patterns in their work and specializations, 10) The social status and privileges of court diviners as essential religious specialists with direct access to royal decision-making processes, 11) The relationship between diviners and ancestor spirits, where diviners served as intermediaries facilitating communication between the living royal court and deceased Shang kings, 12) Archaeological evidence for diviner workshops and bone preparation areas at Yinxu showing the material culture associated with professional divination practice, 13) The evolution of the diviner's role across different periods of the Shang dynasty and how divination practices may have changed over time, 14) Specific examples of named diviners from oracle bone inscriptions and what their recorded activities reveal about the day-to-day practice of court divination.")
WITH OUTPUT BUDGET 3500 tokens, TEMPERATURE 0.1, FORMAT markdown;